The paper deals with visualizing evidence for CNN classification results, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the interpretability of deep learning models, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a new method for visualizing evidence, which involves optimizing the input image, a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of network introspection for debugging and understanding deep convolutional networks, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
